WEBVTT

00:11.011 --> 00:13.179
<i>George Sr. had convinced his wife</i>

00:13.263 --> 00:15.724
<i>to join him in their search
for a son...</i>

00:15.807 --> 00:17.684
Nobody's chasing him.
What's the big deal?

00:17.767 --> 00:19.394
<i>...who thought he'd broken out of prison.</i>

00:19.477 --> 00:21.104
Well,
we just want to find him

00:21.187 --> 00:23.231
before he does something stupid.

00:23.314 --> 00:25.108
<i>Well, stupider.</i>

00:25.191 --> 00:26.735
- My left, your right.
- Your left, my right.

00:26.818 --> 00:29.154
<i>Although, it is the only way</i>
<i>to ride one of those...</i>

00:29.237 --> 00:31.990
We have to get these manacles off.
We have to find a hardware store.

00:32.073 --> 00:33.533
<i>...when you're chained to a guy.</i>

00:33.616 --> 00:35.035
- My right, your right.
- My right, my left.

00:35.118 --> 00:36.619
I remember there's a hardware store...

00:36.703 --> 00:38.455
my left, your right... or a Build-A-Bear

00:38.538 --> 00:40.415
I used to go to, but that was,
like, let me think,

00:40.498 --> 00:42.208
Justin Be-Bear is seven...

00:42.375 --> 00:43.960
that was, like, seven years ago.

00:44.044 --> 00:45.045
Your left, my right.

00:45.128 --> 00:46.629
<i>Why do you think</i>
<i>he'd be at the mall?</i>

00:46.713 --> 00:50.550
Well, the last time Buster ran away,
he came here.

00:50.633 --> 00:52.469
And this is where his favorite stores are.

00:52.552 --> 00:55.180
There's Drink-A-Juice
and there's Paint-A-Plate

00:55.263 --> 00:56.848
and Build-A-Bear and...

00:56.931 --> 00:59.184
Oh, there's a tiny train.

00:59.267 --> 01:01.519
Now, admittedly, he's not 28 anymore,

01:01.603 --> 01:02.687
- but...
- No, you're right.

01:02.854 --> 01:04.938
But don't you think
he would've smelled me by now?

01:05.022 --> 01:07.192
Oh, good point.
Maybe the Popcorn Plantation

01:07.275 --> 01:08.568
is masking your scent.

01:08.651 --> 01:10.945
Ooh, we gotta get you out
of the food court.

01:11.154 --> 01:13.073
<i>Now the story</i>
<i>of a wealthy family</i>

01:13.156 --> 01:16.367
<i>who lost everything, and
the one son who had no choice</i>

01:16.451 --> 01:17.535
<i>but to keep them all together.</i>

01:24.209 --> 01:25.835
<i>It's </i> Arrested Development.

01:30.632 --> 01:32.092
<i>Buster was missing,</i>

01:32.175 --> 01:34.385
<i>and George Sr. was eager
to make it look like</i>

01:34.469 --> 01:37.138
<i>- that was something he cared about...</i>
- Oh, wow!

01:37.222 --> 01:38.515
<i>...in order to woo his wife.</i>

01:38.598 --> 01:39.808
Didn't I used to have one?

01:39.891 --> 01:41.559
Yes, but it was real.

01:41.643 --> 01:44.521
- ♪ <i>Sugarfoot, Sugarfoot</i> ♪
- That's what it was.

01:44.604 --> 01:46.189
- Let's get one.
<i>- Which is how Lucille</i>

01:46.272 --> 01:48.191
<i>- thought of a way...</i>
- Can you make one of those

01:48.274 --> 01:49.651
from a wallet photo?

01:49.734 --> 01:50.902
<i>...to let Buster know</i>

01:50.985 --> 01:52.529
<i>the authorities weren't after him</i>

01:52.612 --> 01:54.280
<i>- and get a little dig in.</i>
- Let's go.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.782
♪ <i>Sugarfoot...</i> ♪

01:56.116 --> 01:57.075
I have a better idea.

01:57.158 --> 01:59.869
Why don't you just pick out
anything you want?

02:00.495 --> 02:02.664
George, we should not
be spending money.

02:02.747 --> 02:05.750
We owe it to the Chinese,
and if we don't get them their money,

02:05.834 --> 02:07.669
they're going to be looking for us.

02:07.752 --> 02:09.586
Well, I wouldn't worry
about that because I have Michael

02:09.669 --> 02:10.755
at the Bluth Company

02:10.964 --> 02:12.841
going through the books,
and he's gonna free up

02:12.924 --> 02:13.925
some cash.

02:14.092 --> 02:16.469
You have Michael looking
through our books?

02:16.886 --> 02:19.764
<i>Where he had recently</i>
<i>discovered and printed...</i>

02:20.014 --> 02:23.643
- A map.
<i>- ...a very provocative piece of evidence.</i>

02:23.726 --> 02:24.811
There's only one way to find out.

02:25.061 --> 02:28.106
<i>And so, Michael set out</i>
<i>to get conclusive evidence</i>

02:28.189 --> 02:30.358
<i>that his parents were building a wall.</i>

02:31.693 --> 02:33.987
<i>Unfortunately, the speed of the printer</i>

02:34.070 --> 02:35.905
<i>made it very clear why</i>

02:35.989 --> 02:38.199
<i>Two Hour Teeth went out of business.</i>

